               <msContents>
                  <summary>Mummy bandages inscribed with extracts from the Book of the Dead and
                     vignettes for a woman called Tai-mu.</summary>
                  <textLang mainLang="egy-Egyh">Egyptian in Hieratic script</textLang>

               </msContents>
               <physDesc>
                  <objectDesc form="sheet">
                     <supportDesc material="other">
                        <support>Linen</support>
                        <extent>Six fragments of linen bandages. The dimensions given are for the
                           largest and smallest fragments respectively.<dimensions type="leaf"
                              unit="mm">
                              <height>59</height>
                              <width>295</width>
                           </dimensions><dimensions type="leaf" unit="mm">
                              <height>53</height>
                              <width>156</width>
                           </dimensions>
                        </extent>
                     </supportDesc>

                  </objectDesc>
                  <handDesc>
                     <handNote>Likely written by one scribe, all in black ink.</handNote>
                  </handDesc>
                  <decoDesc>
                     <decoNote>Only three of the six bandages are illustrated. The first has a
                        vignette of a goddess standing behind a cat wearing a collar, while a woman
                        leans over a scarab beetle. The second has a vignette of a crocodile-headed
                        god holding knives and a praising man stood around a shrine. The third
                        vignette is of a human-headed serpent. All vignettes are drawn in black ink
                        only.</decoNote>
                  </decoDesc>


               </physDesc>
